
[1]virulence

   VIR'ULENCE,'ULENCY, n. [from virulent.]

   1. That renders it extremely active in doing injury; acrimony;
   malignancy; as the virulence of poison.

   2. Acrimony of temper; extreme bitterness or malignity; as the
   virulence of enmity or malice; the virulence of satire; to attack a man
   with virulence.
